The paper deals with a multitask optimization problem and proposes a diffusion strategy for distributed inference over networks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of stochastic approximations and regularization also indicates a possible connection to the Stochastic Optimization (cs.SI) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the focus on graph structures and network performance suggests a potential link to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
